[h2 id=SensitivityWarnings 
	" 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://tasvideos.org/images/sensitivitywarning.png 
	]img
	" Sensitivity Warnings 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://tasvideos.org/images/sensitivitywarning.png 
	]img
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"The yellow 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://tasvideos.org/images/sensitivitywarning.png 
	]img
	" symbol indicates the presence of scenes that may cause visual or aural discomfort, such as rapidly flashing lights, colors, and images, or sudden loud noises. Movies tagged with this symbol will contain explanations in the publication description to further inform the viewer of what they may experience.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" Per 
		[a href=https://web.archive.org/web/20240918171807/https://www.itu.int/dms_pubrec/itu-r/rec/bt/R-REC-BT.1702-3-202311-I!!PDF-E.pdf rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"official guidance
		]a
		", flashing is harmful when it's either 4 or more times per second, or when it lasts 5 seconds or longer.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=A list of all movies with sensitivity warnings can be found here|href=/Movies-sensitivitywarning)
	". If you think a run should be flagged, let us know!
	$LF
]div
[h2 id=ContentWarnings 
	" 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://tasvideos.org/images/contentwarning.png 
	]img
	" Content Warnings 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://tasvideos.org/images/contentwarning.png 
	]img
	$LF
]h2
[div class=p 
	"The red 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=https://tasvideos.org/images/contentwarning.png 
	]img
	" symbol indicates the presence of scenes that may cause mental discomfort and distress due to dark or disturbing subject matter. Movies tagged with this symbol will also contain explanations in the publication description, allowing the viewer to make an informed decision on whether or not to watch the run.
	$LF
]div
[ul 
	[li 
		" This flag indicates age-restriction on the YouTube encode, which has this 
		[a href=https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/2802167?hl=en rel=noopener external nofollow 
			"official guidance
		]a
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[div class=p 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=A list of all movies with content warnings can be found here|href=/Movies-contentwarning)
	". If you think a run should be flagged, let us know!
]div
